column5: 3 buddies and myself headed out to the same spot again.The action did not disappoint.Must of caught over a hundred Perch,nothing else.Ended up keeping 42  3/4 -to just over 1lb fish.What a great day for this time of year.Winds were in excess of 25km's.The anchor hung tough !Week 3 coming up Sat.Here are a couple pics.
Your boat leans to the left. Were you standing on that side or was that bucket that loaded ? LOL  Nice yella bellies Dave.

Your boat leans to the left. Were you standing on that side or was that bucket that loaded ? LOL  Nice yella bellies Dave. I was standing at the back lol.That bucket weighed 38lbs with little water.Fun day I'll say.!
Nice pic of all those perch.  Looks like you had a banana peel beside the bucket.  Is that your secret bait? haha
Looks like a great day of fishing.
fish fry! Awesome -stuff.Hopefully this weekend we don't need winter jackets......
MMM perch one of the best eating fish in the waters.   Art

One of the best for sure,can't believe the water so rough ,the fish turn on.That was a ridiculous day lol.Thanks guys,and Brian,had to grab that pick when the boat was somewhat relaxed.At least I now know the boat can easily handle 25km plus a bit more.Not being stupid,but was still ok for fishing.
Nice feed of jumbos, good job!

Brian,had to grab that pick when the boat was somewhat relaxed.At least I now know the boat can easily handle 25km plus a bit more.Not being stupid,but was still ok for fishing.  Any you wonder why my toon shots are on an angle.LOL  Im looking forward to a perch fry once they come in here and the water cools down.
